```json
{
    "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "description": "Models a keyword used in describing a piece of content.",
    "properties": {
        "frequency": {
            "description": "An optional count of the frequency of the keyword as it appears in the content it describes",
            "type": "integer"
        },
        "keyword": {
            "description": "The keyword used to describe a piece of content",
            "type": "string"
        },
        "score": {
            "description": "An arbitrary weighting to give the keyword",
            "type": "number"
        },
        "tag": {
            "enum": ["noun", "verb", "adjective", "adverb"],
            "description": "The Part of Speech tag for this keyword.",
            "type": "string"
        },
        "tagValue": {
            "description": "A string value representing the tag's value",
            "type": "string"
        }
    },
    "required": [
        "keyword",
        "score"
    ],
    "title": "Keyword",
    "type": "object"
}
```

In the updated schema, I added an `enum` constraint to the `tag` property using the `enum` keyword. This ensures that only one of the allowed tags can be assigned to each keyword. The `tagValue` field is also updated to include a description value for each tag.